      <hedline>
        <hl1>A New Red Sox Curse</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''For Red Sox, the Relief Is Almost Beyond Belief,'' June 4: There must be a New York Times curse. What better explanation can there be when Murray Chass just happens to write a column waxing poetic about Boston's relievers the same day that Hideki Okajima and Jonathan Papelbon each give up a run and the Yankees beat the Sox, 6-5? As a Boston fan, I'm begging you: No more stories about how wonderful the Sox are.</p>
        <p>Lynn Klyde-Silverstein  Denver</p>
      </block>
